In an apparent response to mounting demands from students and opposition groups Indonesian legislators agreed to launch an investigation into former president Soeharto wealth.
Meanwhile State Secretary/Minister Akbar Tanjung reiterated the government seriousness in investigating Soeharto wealth.
The Indonesian government has set up two teams to investigate alleged corruption as his wealth.
However a foreign media estimated Soeharto and his family fortune is worth 40 billion U.S. dollars.
Indonesian Attorney General Soedjono C. Atmonegoro said that an investigation on the wealth of former government officials including former President Soeharto and his family was going on.

